<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - MANIFOLDS AND EXHAUST GAS RECIRCULATION (EGR) - Installation -
        Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR) Valve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26503.4.4" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR) Valve</title>
        <figure id="f2650323" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd17/d1705a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EGR valve assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Large O-ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve group O-rings (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Common pintle shaft</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a large O-ring on the EGR valve.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate two new valve group O-rings with a solution of dish washing soap and water
                (approximately 50/50 mix) and install O-rings on EGR valve.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650348" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd14/d1449.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Seat EGR valve</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">When installing the EGR valve into the intake manifold, make sure the valve is completely
                seated by hand before installing bolts.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Failing to completely seat the EGR valve into the intake manifold, before inserting the
                        mounting bolts, may cause damage to the EGR valve.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650348.1" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD14/D1460.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Insatallation of EGR valve</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 35 bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR valve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">8-pin electrical connector</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thread two M6 x 35 bolts by hand and tighten, alternating between both bolts to the standard
                torque .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect 8-pin electrical connector to EGR valve.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reinstall all safety guards, shields, and covers.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure all tools, cleanliness covers, loose parts, and service equipment are removed from
                the engine work area.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
